    "shortDescription": "Seahorses are the only animals in the world where the father carries the babies. The female deposits eggs into a pouch on the male's belly, and he carries them, feeds them nutrients through his body, and gives birth to up to two thousand tiny seahorses at once. Fun fact: Seahorses can't swim fast at all — but they're expert ambush hunters who hover invisibly among seagrass until prey drifts close."
